🌺 GENERAL DESCRIPTION

The following homework is a Student Management System designed to manage students,
courses, and enrollments within an academic environment. The program allows users
to perform common tasks such as adding and removing students, creating courses,
enrolling students in courses, assigning grades, calculating GPAs, and generating
reports from a menu of options. The program also includes sample data (at least
10 students, 5 courses, and multiple enrollments) to test and demonstrate full
 system functionality.

🌺 BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF EACH CLASS

# PRINCIPAL CLASSES

1. Student.java
Represents a student with personal and academic information such as
student ID, first name, last name, email, GPA, major, and academic year.

2. Course.java
Represents a course with details like course code, course name,
 credits, instructor, maximum enrollment, and course prerequisites.

3. StudentManager.java
Manages a collection ofl students in the system using an ArrayList
 and provides operations such as add, remove, find, filter students
 by specific majors, filter students by specific university year,
 filter honor students based on a minimum GPA, average GPA of all
 students, average GPA of all student from specific, total students and
 list all students with their relevant information.

4. Enrollment.java
Represents the relationship between a student and a course, including
enrollment ID, student ID, course Code, grade and semester information.

5. EnrollmentManager.java
Manages student enrollments, create enrollments, drop enrollments,
find enrollments, list students enrollments, check courses capacity,
assigns grades to students list enrollments by courses, number of
enrollments, calculates student GPA based on their grade on courses,
and list all enrollments.

6. CourseManager.java
Manages a collection of courses using an ArrayList and provides
operations to add, find, remove, filter courses by instructor,
available courses to enroll students, list all courses, and total
number of courses.

7. ReportGenerator.java
Generates reports such as student summaries, course enrollments,
major summaries, and honor roll summary.

8. StudentManagementSystemMain.java
Main class with sample students, courses, prerequisites, and enrollments
created to test functionality of the student management system. Includes
a menu with multiples options that user can performance into the management system.

# SECONDARY CLASSES

9. ArrayListOperationsDemo.java
Demonstrates ArrayList operations like conversion, subList, sorting,
and searching. Also classes that implement comparators to sort in
descending order students GPA and Last Name.

10. ArrayListvsArrayDemo.java
Compares ArrayList and array performance, including add, remove, resize,
and access time with a report of the differences between both. Also,
includes a summary explaining from my understanding when to use
ArrayList or Array.

11. ArrayListUtils.java
Provides generic utility methods for ArrayLists like find maximum,
reverse, merge, filter, filter above, displaying lists, and numeric
operations like sum, average, and numeric operations with use of
wildcards types. Also includes a main testing functions and operations.

12. GenericList<T>
A generic list wrapper around ArrayList with basic operations like add,
remove, get, size, isEmpty, clear, addAll, and contains. Also, includes
a main testing of all basic operations and using Generics.

13. GenericStack<T>
A generic stack implemented using ArrayList with functions like
push, pop, peek, size, isEmpty, and clear operations. Also includes
a main testing of all stack operations.

14. GenericQueue<T>
A generic queue implemented using ArrayList with enqueue, dequeue,
peek, isEmpty, and size operations. Also includes a main testing of
all of the queue operations.

15. Pair<K, V>
A generic class that stores two related values, first and second,
with getters, setters, toString, equals and hashCode. Includes a
main testing of the functionality using different types of ArrayList
to show generics.

🌺 HOW TO COMPILE AND RUN THE PROGRAM

To compile and run the program, click and make sure to be inside
the file “StudentManagementSystemMain.java” and click on the Run
button. The program will be compiled and it will start showing some
messages indicating that sample data was created (students, courses,
enrollments) and the menu of options to user test.

🌺 DESIGN DECISIONS I MADE
I decided to use the alternative counter base to fix the “hidden problem” on
 enrollStudent() method inside EnrollmentManeger.java class to create enrollmentIds
  for students.
In the options menu, I decided to add additional actions such as "List
all courses" to get a specific overview of all courses and "List all
enrollments" to get the StudentId, EnrollmentId generated using the counter base
and the full name of the enrolled student to make things easier when I'm
demonstrating the menu functions during the recording.
I connected EnrollmentManager to CourseManager on EnrollmentManager so each
class has its own responsibility. At first, my enrollStudent method was not
working correctly according to the instructions. I realized it was because
I needed to check if the course exists and if the course was already full
before enrolling a student. I added a reference to CourseManager inside
EnrollmentManager to allowed me to validate the course properly before creating
the enrollment, and after that the method worked as expected.
I added to the design  check like if something is not found, if
ArrayList is null, If is empty, and some more possible cases.


