🌺 WHAT I LEARNED ABOUT ARRAYLIST AND GENERICS

Array is better to use when you know how many elements you need to store.
ArrayList is better to use when you need flexibility in sizing..
ArrayList can do operations like add, resize and remove elements easier
than Array which has this limitations at least you do those operation manually.
ArrayList just works with wrapper classes and objects
Generics lists have methods like AddAll to combine two lists of the same type.
Generics improve type safety because they prevent adding the wrong type of object.

🌺 COMPARISON OF ARRAYLIST VS ARRAY LIST ON MY EXPERIENCE
ArrayList can add multiple elements because it is dynamic sizing
(auto-resize while you add elements) and uses useful methods to do it like add().
Array has size limitation because it is fixed size. This complicates
adding multiple elements without being aware of the size of the array.
ArrayList can remove elements from any part of the list without problems
using remove()
I can not remove from array an element of the middle because arrays have
fixed size. Removing an element from the middle could require manually
shifting all the remaining elements to remove a specific element.
